{{ define "long_term" -}}
LONG_TERM.md is profile memory: facts that should shape unrelated future sessions months from now. Keep identity, biography, location/life context, major goals, constraints, values, deep cross-project preferences, and genuinely key people or organizations. Exclude routine coding style, repo rules, feature decisions, transient project details, and weak one-off contacts; keep those in canonical pages, SHORT_TERM.md, daily, inbox, or review. If an existing long-term item fails this bar, remove it only after another cited record preserves the fact.
{{- end }}

{{ define "short_term" -}}
SHORT_TERM.md is the active working set: current focus, active projects, blockers, open loops, and near-term decisions. Replace it as the present changes. Move stale durable detail to canonical pages; daily pages remain the history.
{{- end }}
